This paper deals with communication theory and information theory, specifically with the use of probabilistic shaping schemes for polar codes to enable power-efficient signaling for on-off keying. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with communication systems and signal processing, which suggests the category cs.COMM (Communication and Networking). The use of joint distribution matching and forward error correction in polar codes suggests the category cs.SI (Signal Processing). The paper also deals with numerical simulations, which suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with optimization and performance analysis, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
